From jeremy.miles at gmail.com  Thu Feb  9 19:37:34 2017
From: jeremy.miles at gmail.com (Jeremy Miles)
Date: Thu, 09 Feb 2017 18:37:34 +0000
Subject: [R-sig-teaching] Cronbach's Alpha Values
In-Reply-To: <CAHDp66DA=XRApwKneJ97KCf8dgNjZodf0TOgm_9yOO65DuLokw@mail.gmail.com>
References: <CAHDp66DA=XRApwKneJ97KCf8dgNjZodf0TOgm_9yOO65DuLokw@mail.gmail.com>
Message-ID: <CAMtGSx=kN15Q8eOODw=Gbszp+-yUWa7naBReJ1JfTLma8ig=kw@mail.gmail.com>

Almost always that you've made a mistake and haven't reversed some items
that should have been reversed. (Some software will do that automatically).

Use check.keys=TRUE, and the alpha function (in the psych package) will
automatically reverse items if that needs to be done.

J

