From joel at joelschwartz.com  Wed Mar  8 18:02:55 2017
From: joel at joelschwartz.com (Joel Schwartz)
Date: Wed, 8 Mar 2017 09:02:55 -0800
Subject: [R-sig-teaching] Reverse the scoring of some Columns of a Data
	Set
In-Reply-To: <CAE9stmcJ0VW=4QOZWbF89v_qJu8tkkM+DEK1VZKFOeAjfzCCGw@mail.gmail.com>
References: <CAE9stmcJ0VW=4QOZWbF89v_qJu8tkkM+DEK1VZKFOeAjfzCCGw@mail.gmail.com>
Message-ID: <05A396B0-2AD4-4AD1-A27A-A9F9730BFC59@joelschwartz.com>

If your data frame is called df then you can reverse the scoring by doing df$x1 =  rev(df$x1).

To do multiple columns, you can do:

df[ , paste0(?x?,1:3)] = lapply(df[ , paste0(?x?,1:3)], rev)

